                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d898">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 891.001.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Russell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-09-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 23, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The President has cabled to the Shah his sympathy upon the death of the Regent,
                    and the Secretary of State has cabled similarly to the <pb facs="0936" n="824"
                        xml:id="pg_824"/> minister for foreign affairs. If you have not already done
                    so, you will convey to the minister for foreign affairs proper expression of
                    sympathy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Adee.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
